Key Match Events: The Texas Rangers secured an 11-4 victory over the Houston Astros in game seven of the ALCS, advancing to their first World Series since 2011.
Corey Seager hit an early home run to give Texas an early lead.
The Rangers scored four runs in the top of the fourth inning to extend their lead.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Texas Rangers will host the first four games of the World Series at their home stadium in Arlington.
